runs.comm: sharp bounce for Mills outside off stump from a length, and also a bit of away shape, left alone
Zimbabwe are away, he gets forward and across and pushes a length ball behind point
pushed on the off side off the front foot
straightening after pitching on a length outside off, Mills delivering from wide of the crease, he stays cautiously in the crease and guides it to point
goes for a drive now as mills pitched it further up, but without much foot movement and the ball rolls away to extra cover
Mills thinks there is something here, Chibhabha misses an attempted cut off a short and wide one, the keeper does not appeal, the slips don't as well, did not seem to be any bat there
bit of away shape and he floats his first ball full and on middle and leg from wide of the crease, played out to midwicket
goes full again, on the stumps, there is some straightening again on the ball, pushed away to mid on
inside edge as he looks to drive again without moving the feet much, inside edge rolls behind square leg, Bracewell keeping it full again
for the first time he pitches on a length and Masakadza plonks front foot out and smashes him over mid off
tries to go hard at a length ball outside off but mistimes it to point
does not quite get hold of a pitched up ball, still managed to get enough power on it but the bowler got down in time to take pace off it
Masakadza has charged out to a length ball and holed out to mid off, Nathan running to his left and taking a fine tumbling catch around deep extra cover
some bounce for Mills as he gets it shape away from outside off, left alone
the second time he has been beaten on the attempted cut, this one was not wide enough as the previous one, he tried to arch back and guide it past point, missed
Chibhabha has connected this time, not that short and into the body, he has made some room and teed off over mid on
he is having some trouble with the short ones outside off stump, the third time he has missed out on the cut, this one was more an attempted dab
he likes this length, the fuller one, gets front foot moving forward and squeezes the drive past Mills
hurled on a length close to off and holding its line, Taylor dead-bats it quietly
Taylor clears mid off, not by much, but he will get the boundary, it was moving away from him, but there was width and he stepped forward and went through with the swing, got enough on it
tries to belt another one through the off side, but this time the ball rolls along the ground to mid off
this one did not hold its line, it went straight on to the pads with the angle, Taylor managed to adjust, crouch and dab it towards midwicket
oh well, he has put in a lot of shoulder on this one, short ball takes off at the batsman who gets down on the knee and takes head out of the way

ends the over with another bouncer, but this one is outside off and he easily lets it go, Mills lures him in to the shot with one that is pitched up and moves away, Chibhabha throws the bat at it and Baz fumbles with the thick edge a couple of times before tumbling on the ground, ball in gloves
Chibhabha's urge to drive without moving his feet has led to his fall

almost another one as Mills lets rip with the short ball that gets up at Mutizwa's throat, he goes for a weak pull, which ends up saving him as the ball falls in front of Bracewell running in from long leg
pushed on the off side for one
inside edge almost drops on the stumps, stays in the crease to one that comes in with the angle, he tries to play it with an angled blade and almost chops it on
troubles him again with a back of a length ball that comes in, he tries to dab it to third man from too close to the body, beaten
quietly dropped in front of mid on for a quick single

almost a run out, shortish one pulled through midwicket, they took on the throw from the deep for the third, no way non-striker would have made it in time, but Oram was not around at the crease to take the throw as it came in
steered to third man for one
length ball pushed in the air towards cover
now it is Mutizwa's turn to be beaten by a short and wide one outside off as he misses with an attempted dab
poor delivery and Mutizwa capitalises, short down the leg side and he swivels to help it wide of short fine leg
takes a single now to keep strike, not a particularly good over from Oram
on the pads, pushed in the air in front of square leg
goes looking for a sweep to a flat and full one and misses
fine shot, only a single through as there is man at sweeper cover, making room and driving inside out through cover
nudged off the front foot towards midwicket
Taylor does a bit of a dash down the track and gives this a good thump, there is a man at long off
pushed to mid on for one
comes slowly off the deck but some width outside off, he slices it to third man
shuffles across and gets outside the crease but is tucked up for room with one that is angled in, can only block
slows it down considerably and it hardly gets up as Taylor lines up the pull, rolls under his swing
fetches the pull from a long way outside off now, but mistimes it and the man at deep midwicket gets to it
he is shuffling and standing almost outside off eyeing midwicket but Oram follow him there and he dinks it close to the stumps for one
Oram is dealing in slower ones here, this one is of the short kind and it rises loopily at the batsman who does not get any sort of timing on the attempted pull, falls near square leg
steps down the track but can only push in the air past extra cover as Woodcock pushes it through
this will go, short and wide outside off, Taylor hammers it and gets the placement to the right of sweeper cover
the shot was one again, but Taylor could not place it past sweeper cover

gone leg before, Zimbabwe are stuttering, got a long way across but it missed one that straightened from wide of the crease to catch him in front, even as the appeal was on, Taylor took off for a run, Brendon got to the ball and threw it towards the bowler, even as Woodcock was getting rid of the bails, the umpire finally gave Mutizwa out
pushed defensively off the front foot
almost another run out but Taylor makes it at the striker's end attempting a sharp run
shovelled through square leg off the pad
Taylor takes on Nathan and swings him through midwicket, picked it up from well outside off, did not get the elevation he was looking for but still got it in the gap
played out towards midwicket
comes down the track but Nathan tucks him up with one fired in and he pushes it back
Nathan coming back well after the boundary, Taylor cannot find any space on the leg side with a nudge
finally hits it down to long on for one
fine save on the deep extra cover boundary, super shot from Taylor as he charges out and lofts pleasingly over the off side infield inside out
very full one, he digs it back down the track
shuffles and gets lot of bat on the flick in front of square leg, for one
quicker one pushed through, slides in, he manages to tickle it towards square leg
holds it up in the air, much slower, he pushes at it and gets it through point
slapped through extra cover for a single
leaves the crease again, the trajectory is too flat and he whips it towards midwicket
Waller launches this one over deep midwicket, helpful low full toss, he goes down on a knee and hammers it off the middle of the blade
dabbed on the off side
tries to pick him up from outside off, cannot get enough under the ball, and it loops half way down the track
Waller finds deep square leg, bends the knee and swings well with the turn but picks out the man in the deep, the shot went a bit too flat in the air
full one worked down to long on with the turn
starts with a no ball, decent delivery though, full and angled outside off, he dabs it softy on the off side
can't do anything with the free hit, Taylor has a swing across the line and gets hit on the pad as Franklin slows it down
slapped towards point for one
that is a very fine shot, he has played some well-timed ones today, places front foot down the track, Franklin slants it across and Taylor lifts it straight over the bowler
driven neatly wide of extra cover for one, Franklin bowls another no-ball
now Coventry misses out off the free hit, goes too hard at it and misses the swing completely, getting hit on the pad
he's let this one go outside off after making some room and shaping up to have a go at it
tentatively prods and edges a slower one towards point for a single
is cramped for room with one that homes in on leg stump, manages to push it with a straight bat past the non-striker
opens the face and looks for a single, but stops immediately as he finds point advancing on the ball
cannot get hold of this pitched up ball, swings it along the ground to long on
well bowled, finds lots of bounce from back of  a length, Coventry hops looks to slap it through extra cover from the crease, the bounce beats him
shuffles across, trying to make some room, but Mills gets it dead straight, has to block
driven down to long off, only a single
full one fired in from wide of the crease, he almost falls over as he nudges it towards square leg
swung without any timing towards square leg
speared in on leg stump and an inside edge ruins what was a good ball, gets him four fine on the leg side
beaten outside off as Woodcock shifts the line
had Woodcock collected the ball, Coventry was gone even though he put in the dive, they had gone for the single with a push to extra cover
Taylor ruins Woodcock's over further with a superbly placed shot that comfortably beats sweeper cover
Coverntry has holed out to extra cover, charged out looking for the straight boundary, Nathan pushed it quick and flat, and he mistimed it high towards extra cover who settled under it
Nathan saves the single with a scrambling dive to his right
full delivery clipped past a diving midwicket
that kept a tad low, he stayed back and worked it towards midwicket
Nathan saves yet another single with a dash to his right, this full toss was pushed pretty firmly but he got a hand to it, and Taylor had to get back
fired in the blockhole, he gets bat down and jams it away on the leg side
drives a full delivery floated up wide outside off to sweeper cover, another no-ball from NZ
opens up, goes deep in the crease and swings a full delivery through midwicket, the man in the deep gets to it
clipped through midwicket, Williamson fumbles as he runs across from long on and Taylor comes back for two
Elton has arrived and started finding the gaps right away, this time he drives a full one well wide of sweeper cover who has to put in a slide to stop it
well done, bends the knees and easily gets out of the line of a short ball slanted in
another short one, Elton was late in getting out of the way, got the bat down and let it sail past in the end
gets away with one that had some width on it, Elton cranks up but finds extra cover with the drive
walks across and scoops a slow back of a length ball wide of long leg for two
short from Oram but hardly gets up off the deck and Taylor cannot find placement on the pull, hits it straight to deep midwicket
another slower one dug in outside off, Elton waits for a long time for it to arrive and slaps it, but point takes pace off it with a dive
he was setting himself up for the big shot but Oram hurried him into a defensive push with a quicker one angled in on the stumps
full delivery but he can only push it down to long on
again Oram does not give even an inch worth of width, tucked in front of square leg
gets it very full outside off and Taylor does not get much bat on it as he swings down to long on
lines up the midwicket boundary with a big heave but Bracewell bowls it pretty wide outside off and Elton cannot get bat to it
this is a tight over so far, gets it right in the blockhole a foot outside off, and elton can only dig it out
Bracewell does not get it full enough by some inches, the line is just outside off and Elton instantly tees off over the bowler
Bracewell bowls another well-directed short ball that comes in to Elton who cannot find any connection with a belatedly-attempted pull
Elton has lifted this one high and straight to Ross Taylor at extra cover, it was a low full toss but he got too much underneath it and scooped it up in the air as he tried to go down the ground
swing and a miss to a wide one outside off
backs away and has a slog but it rolls off the underedge to Oram who sends the batsman scurrying back with a throw, that misses in the end
Chakabva walks, he has bent the knee and had one last go at Oram, only finding an underedge  on this length ball on its way to Brendon

Oram is all over Zimbabwe, he bowls a slow short one outside off that is dropped softly for a single, runs towards the ball, turns around and fires in the throw, hitting the non-striker's end, the batsman was in by that time
he has banged in the short ball halfway up the track and it has climbed too high and sailed over the batsman
fifty for Taylor with a couple on the off side,  a fumble allows the second, he is the reason they have managed to get past 100 with his team-mates holing out all around the field

Oram finally has his run-out, Taylor threw his bat at a low full toss, but Oram's big frame got down and stopped the ball, he recovered well to lob the ball on to the non-striker's stumps, catching Utseya well out of his ground
